# =============================================================================
# mambakkam.net — production env
#
# Copy to .env.demo and edit. scripts/launch/provision.sh does this for you
# on first run; subsequent edits are manual.
#
# Astro is a static-site generator: env vars are baked in at BUILD time, not
# read at runtime. So this file is consumed by `docker compose --env-file
# .env.demo up --build`, which exposes the values as build args inside the
# Dockerfile (extend Dockerfile to pass them through if/when needed).
#
# At launch (May 16) only the analytics ID is meaningful. SMTP / contact form
# placeholders are kept here so the future contact-form change is a one-line
# env edit, not a re-architecture.
# =============================================================================

# ── Site identity ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SITE_URL=https://mambakkam.net

# ── Analytics (Plausible recommended; GA4 also supported) ──────────────────
# Set ONE of the two; leave the other blank.
PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN=mambakkam.net
GA4_MEASUREMENT_ID=

# ── SMTP (for the future contact form / newsletter) ───────────────────────
# Demo posture: NO app-originated email. Inbound goes through Cloudflare
# Email Routing (forwarded to personal Gmail); outbound is Gmail send-as in
# alias mode — neither path uses these env vars.
#
# When you ship a contact form, sign up for a paid mail provider (Zoho Mail
# Lite ~$12/yr, Migadu ~$19/yr, Fastmail ~$36/yr), generate an App Password,
# and fill in the four lines below. Provider examples:
#   Zoho Mail Lite:   smtp.zoho.com  port 465 SSL
#   Migadu:           smtp.migadu.com port 465 SSL
#   Fastmail:         smtp.fastmail.com port 465 SSL
# Keep mode 600 on .env.demo.
SMTP_HOST=
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_USE_SSL=true
SMTP_USER=siva@mambakkam.net
SMTP_PASSWORD=
SMTP_FROM_NAME=Mambakkam
